1 tial facility designated under this section shall comply with the requirements of section 3 of
2 this 2026 Act.
3 (b) A hospital, as defined in ORS 442.015, or a hospital-affiliated clinic, as defined in ORS
4 442.612, that is designated as an additional caregiver under this section is not subject to the
5 requirements of section 3 of this 2026 Act.
6 SECTION 6. ORS 475C.792 is amended to read:
7 475C.792. (1)(a) The Oregon Health Authority shall establish by rule a marijuana grow site
8 registration system to track and regulate the production of marijuana by a registry identification
9 cardholder or a person designated by the registry identification cardholder to produce marijuana for
10 the registry identification cardholder.
11 (b) Except as provided in paragraph (c) of this subsection, a person may not produce marijuana
12 unless the person is registered under this section.
13 (c) Paragraph (b) of this subsection does not apply to the production of marijuana as provided
14 in ORS 475C.005 to 475C.525 or as otherwise provided for by the statutory laws of this state.
15 (2) Rules adopted under this section must require an applicant for a registry identification card,
16 or a registry identification cardholder who produces marijuana or who designates another person
17 to produce marijuana, to submit an application to the authority containing the following information
18 at the time of making an application under ORS 475C.783 (2), renewing a registry identification card
19 under ORS 475C.783 (6)(b), or notifying the authority of a change under ORS 475C.783 (6)(a):
20 (a) The name of the person responsible for the marijuana grow site;
21 (b) Proof that the person is 21 years of age or older;
22 (c) The information required under ORS 475C.831;
23 (d) The address of the marijuana grow site; and
24 (e) Any other information that the authority considers necessary to track the production of
25 marijuana under ORS 475C.770 to 475C.919.
26 (3)(a) The authority shall conduct a criminal records check under ORS 181A.195 of any person
27 whose name is submitted under this section as the person responsible for a marijuana grow site.
28 (b) A person convicted of a Class A or Class B felony under ORS 475.752 to 475.920 for the
29 manufacture or delivery of a controlled substance in Schedule I or Schedule II may not act as or
30 be designated a person responsible for a marijuana grow site for two years from the date of con-
31 viction.
32 (c) A person convicted more than once of a Class A or Class B felony under ORS 475.752 to
33 475.920 for the manufacture or delivery of a controlled substance in Schedule I or Schedule II may
34 not act as or be designated a person responsible for a marijuana grow site.
35 (4) Subject to subsection (11) of this section, the authority shall issue a marijuana grow site
36 registration card if the requirements of subsections (2) and (3) of this section and ORS 475C.831 are
37 met.
38 (5) A person who holds a marijuana grow site registration card under this section must display
39 the card at the marijuana grow site at all times.
40 (6) A marijuana grow site registration card must be obtained and posted for each registry
41 identification cardholder for whom marijuana is being produced at a marijuana grow site.
42 (7)(a) All seeds, immature marijuana plants, mature marijuana plants and usable marijuana as-
43 sociated with the production of marijuana for a registry identification cardholder by a person re-
44 sponsible for a marijuana grow site are the property of the registry identification cardholder.
45 (b) All seeds, immature marijuana plants, mature marijuana plants and usable marijuana asso-
[5]

HB 4142
1 ciated with the production of marijuana for a registry identification cardholder by a person re-
2 sponsible for a marijuana grow site must be transferred to the registry identification cardholder
3 upon the request of the registry identification cardholder.
4 (c) All usable marijuana associated with the production of marijuana for a registry identification
5 cardholder by a person responsible for a marijuana grow site must be transferred to a marijuana
6 processing site upon the request of the registry identification cardholder. For purposes of this par-
7 agraph, a request to transfer usable marijuana constitutes an assignment of the right to possess the
8 usable marijuana.
9 (d) All seeds, immature marijuana plants and usable marijuana associated with the production
10 of marijuana for a registry identification cardholder by a person responsible for a marijuana grow
11 site must be transferred to a medical marijuana dispensary upon request of the registry identifica-
12 tion cardholder. For purposes of this paragraph, a request to transfer seeds, immature marijuana
13 plants or usable marijuana constitutes an assignment of the right to possess the seeds, immature
14 marijuana plants or usable marijuana.
15 (e) Information related to transfers made under this subsection must be submitted to the au-
16 thority in the manner required by ORS 475C.795.
17 (8) A registry identification cardholder, or the designated primary caregiver of a registry
18 identification cardholder, may reimburse a person responsible for a marijuana grow site for all costs
19 associated with the production of marijuana for the registry identification cardholder.
20 (9) The authority may inspect:
21 (a) The marijuana grow site of a person designated to produce marijuana by a registry identifi-
22 cation cardholder to ensure compliance with this section and ORS 475C.795 and 475C.806 and any
23 rule adopted under this section and ORS 475C.795 and 475C.806; and
24 (b) The records of the marijuana grow site of a person designated to produce marijuana by a
25 registry identification cardholder to ensure compliance with this section and ORS 475C.795 and any
26 rule adopted under this section and ORS 475C.795.
27 (10) The authority may refuse to register a registry identification cardholder or a designee under
28 this section or may suspend or revoke the registration of a person responsible for a marijuana grow
29 site if the authority determines that the applicant or the person responsible for a marijuana grow
30 site violated a provision of ORS 475C.770 to 475C.919, a rule adopted under ORS 475C.770 to
31 475C.919 or an ordinance adopted pursuant to ORS 475C.827.
32 (11) The authority may require a person responsible for a marijuana grow site, prior to issuing
33 a marijuana grow site registration card under subsection (4) of this section, to pay a fee reasonably
34 calculated to pay costs incurred under this section and ORS 475C.795 and 475C.856.
35 (12) When submitting an application for renewal of registration under this section, the applicant
36 or person responsible for the marijuana grow site shall, if the applicant or person is not the owner
37 of the premises for which the registration is being renewed, submit with the application the owner’s
38 written signature, witnessed by a notary public, confirming ownership of the premises and consent-
39 ing to the applicant’s or person’s use of the premises for the purpose of a marijuana grow site, if
40 the owner’s consent to the use of the premises is expired.
41 SECTION 7. ORS 475C.883 is amended to read:
42 475C.883. Except as provided in ORS 475C.886, a person, or an organization or residential
43 facility described in ORS 475C.791, engaged in or assisting in the medical use of marijuana is ex-
44 empt from the criminal laws of this state for possession, delivery or manufacture of marijuana, aid-
45 ing and abetting another in the possession, delivery or manufacture of marijuana, or any other
[6]

HB 4142
1 criminal offense in which possession, delivery or manufacture of marijuana is an element if:
2 (1) The person holds a registry identification card.
3 (2) The person has applied for a registry identification card under ORS 475C.783 and the person
4 has proof of written documentation described in ORS 475C.783 (2)(a) and proof of the date on which
5 the person submitted the application to the Oregon Health Authority. An exemption under this
6 subsection applies only until the authority approves or denies the application.
7 (3)(a) The person is designated as a primary caregiver under ORS 475C.789.
8 (b) The organization or residential facility is designated as an additional caregiver under
9 ORS 475C.791, or the person is employed by or has been contracted with an organization or
10 residential facility that is designated as an additional caregiver under ORS 475C.791.
11 (4) The person is responsible for or is employed by a marijuana grow site registered under ORS
12 475C.792.
13 (5) The person owns, is responsible for, or is employed by, a marijuana processing site.
14 (6) The person owns, is responsible for, or is employed by, a medical marijuana dispensary.
15 SECTION 8. ORS 475C.916 is amended to read:
16 475C.916. A nurse licensed under ORS 678.040 to 678.101 may discuss the medical use of
17 marijuana with a person with whom the nurse has a patient-provider relationship. The Oregon
18 State Board of Nursing may not impose a civil penalty or take other disciplinary action
19 against a nurse who engages in a discussion as described in this section.
20 SECTION 9. (1) Prior to the operative date specified in section 10 of this 2026 Act, the
21 Oregon Health Authority may conditionally designate an organization or residential facility
22 described in ORS 475C.791 as an additional caregiver.
23 (2) An organization or residential facility described in ORS 475C.791 or conditionally des-
24 ignated under subsection (1) of this section shall:
25 (a) Create the written policy required under section 3 of this 2026 Act not later than June
26 30, 2027; and
27 (b) Make available to staff the educational training required under section 3 of this 2026
28 Act not later December 31, 2027.
29 (3) If an organization or residential facility designated under ORS 475C.791 or condi-
30 tionally designated under subsection (1) of this section does not meet the requirements of
31 subsection (2) of this section, the authority shall remove the designation from the organiza-
32 tion or residential facility.
33 SECTION 10. (1) Sections 2 and 3 of this 2026 Act and the amendments to ORS 475C.777,
34 475C.791, 475C.792, 475C.883 and 475C.916 by sections 4 to 8 of this 2026 Act become operative
35 on January 1, 2027.
36 (2) The Oregon Health Authority may take any action before the operative date specified
37 in subsection (1) of this section that is necessary to enable the authority to exercise, on and
38 after the operative date specified in subsection (1) of this section, all of the duties, functions
39 and powers conferred on the authority by sections 2 and 3 of this 2026 Act and the amend-
40 ments to ORS 475C.777, 475C.791, 475C.792, 475C.883 and 475C.916 by sections 4 to 8 of this
41 2026 Act.
42 SECTION 11. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
43 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
